Day-4
 Conditional Statements:
--->To make the set instructions(block of code)(conditional statements) execute only when the given condition is true
--->used to decide whether the code has to be executed or skip based on the given condition
--->Is executed in a sequence(Line-By-Line)
	* Block of Code: set of Instructions
	* Condition: An expression that evaluates an result(True or False)
	* Ex:console.log(5>6)		
	
---->Methods:
	* If
	* If-else
	* else if
	* Switch
	* Ternary Operator

---->IF: only one possible condition. If the condition is true it will be executed or it will skip.
		Synatx: if(condition){
			  block of code
			}
---->
